        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 8:45PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 845 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles north of Rutherfordton, moving southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Thermal City, Union Mills, and Shingle Hollow.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
